we can use existing tools to create a prototype of Comshell;

; sudo pacman -S xorg-server xorg-xinit xf86-video-{intel,nouveau,amdgpu} compton
; sudo pacman -S i3-wm i3status emacs mpv

; nano ~/.bash_profile
  startx
; nano ~/.xinitrc
  exec i3
; mkdir -p ~/.config/i3
; cp proto/i3.config ~/.config/i3/config
; mkdir -p ~/.config/i3status
; cp proto/i3status.config ~/.config/i3status/config

; mkdir ~/.emacs.d
; cp proto/init.el ~/.emacs.d/init.el
ELisp is terrible as a programming language,
  but it's pretty good as a command_line interface (ie as a shell, like Bash);

; sudo pacman -S gjs webkit2gtk gst-plugins-{base,good,bad} gst-libav
XDG_CACHE_HOME=project-path/.cache
XDG_CONFIG_HOME=project-path/.cache
XDG_DATA_HOME=project-path/.cache
